# SpecialCarer — Cursor rules
# These rules apply to every AI-assisted edit in this repository.

## Project identity
- Domain: UK on-demand and scheduled care marketplace (SpecialCarer.com).
- Stack: Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict, Supabase (Postgres + RLS + Auth + Storage), Tailwind, Vercel.
- Mobile: Capacitor iOS overlay served from the same Next.js app.

## Hard policies (CodeRabbit blocks PRs that violate these)

### UK-only regional gating
- Every Supabase query against `caregivers`, `cities`, or `coverage` MUST filter `country = "GB"` OR be gated on `process.env.US_REGION_ENABLED === "true"`.
- Public profile routes 404 non-GB carers.
- Default `country` value in new migrations is `'GB'`.

### Vendor naming
- The DBS check vendor must be referred to as "DBS" in code, comments, and JSDoc.
- The strings "Checkr" and "uCheck" MUST NOT appear as a vendor reference anywhere in source. Inner URLs (`https://api.ucheck.co.uk/v1`) are permitted as default values only.
- Env vars: prefer `DBS_*` names. `UCHECK_*` legacy env vars are accepted as fallback only.

### Brand
- Colors: teal `#039EA0` (primary), peach `#F4A261` (accent), cream `#F4EFE6` (surface), ink `#0F1416` (text). No other brand colors in UI code.
- DO NOT use `text-emerald-*`, `text-rose-*`, or any non-brand Tailwind palette class. Use arbitrary values: `text-[#039EA0]` or tokens.
- Font: Plus Jakarta Sans only. No other web fonts.
- Buttons: primary action uses teal background or teal border.

### Privacy & PII
- NEVER log DOB, NI number, DBS certificate number, full postcode, address line 1/2, bank account details, or passport number to console or Sentry.
- All Sentry events go through `beforeSend` scrub in `sentry.client.config.ts` — extend that list if adding new sensitive fields.
- PostHog session replay is denylisted on `/dashboard/vetting/*`, `/m/dbs/*`, `/m/profile/vetting/*`. Don't add capture on those routes.
- Add `data-ph-no-capture` to any new element rendering sensitive data.

### Commits
- Use Conventional Commit prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `refactor:`.
- Scope: lower-case feature area in parens, e.g. `feat(dbs): ...`, `fix(reviews): ...`.
- Bot identity for automated commits: `bot@specialcarer.com` / `SpecialCarer Bot`.

### Migrations
- Place in `supabase/migrations/<unix_timestamp>_<slug>.sql`.
- All policies must include RLS.
- Reversible where possible.
- Backfill data inside the migration when adding NOT NULL columns.

### Testing
- Test files live next to source as `*.test.ts` or under `__tests__/`.
- Add every new test file path to the `test` script in `package.json` (the project does not auto-discover).
- Run: `npm test` after every meaningful change.

### Type safety
- TypeScript strict. No `any` without an inline justification comment.
- Prefer Zod for runtime validation on API route inputs.
- Supabase responses always check `error` field — never fail-open.

## Patterns to follow

### Carer readiness
- `src/lib/care/profile.ts:computeReadiness()` is the canonical "publishable" check. Don't duplicate it inline.
- `getVettingSummary()` returns the admin-side vetting state (References / Skills / Video / Course / DBS).
- Carer self-publish is intentionally separate from admin "is_fully_vetted" — don't conflate them.

### API route conventions
- All `src/app/api/m/**` routes return JSON `{ ok: true, data }` on success, `{ ok: false, error: "<short stable string>" }` on error. NEVER return raw `e.message` to the client.
- Auth: get user via `supabaseServer.auth.getUser()`. Return 401 with `{ ok: false, error: "unauthenticated" }` if no user.
- Admin routes: `src/app/api/admin/**` additionally check `profiles.role === 'admin'`.

### Mobile vs web
- `/m/*` routes are the Capacitor-served mobile flow.
- `/dashboard/*` is the desktop web flow.
- They share components from `src/components/`.
- When changing one, consider whether the other needs the same change.

### Stripe
- Test mode keys for dev. Production keys only via Vercel env vars.
- Seeker memberships: `STRIPE_PRODUCT_*` env-var pattern in `src/lib/memberships/types.ts`. Carer memberships will follow the same pattern.

## Don'ts
- DO NOT auto-merge PRs.
- DO NOT modify `.coderabbit.yaml` without explicit user approval.
- DO NOT add new top-level routes without checking the existing route map.
- DO NOT bypass RLS by using the service-role key in client code.
- DO NOT add billing/payment fields to a user-facing form without a Stripe Element.

## When in doubt
- Surgical PRs > bundled. One concern per PR.
- If a request would violate any rule above, push back and ask for clarification before implementing.
